<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1840010-is-there-anything-inappropriate-in-this">Is there anything inappropriate in this book? I would love to read this, but I don&#39;t want to read that if so.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1840010'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F469901.Mr_Perfect">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1840010-is-there-anything-inappropriate-in-this">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1840010-is-there-anything-inappropriate-in-this">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6682409-nikki"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1609864754i/6682409._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6682409-nikki">Nikki</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Some pretty racy scenes, although that&apos;s not the main focus of the story. I&apos;m not much for that either but the mystery part was intriguing. I would pr<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Some pretty racy scenes, although that's not the main focus of the story. I'm not much for that either but the mystery part was intriguing. I would probably say to skip if you are worried about inappropriate content. Hope that helps!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
